  "summary": "Malicious code in @wagni_bot/ethereum-wallet (npm)",
  "details": "On install, the package runs postinstall.js which performs host fingerprinting (hostname, username, cwd) and then hunts for cryptocurrency wallet files (Solana id.json, Ethereum keystore, Bitcoin/Litecoin wallet.dat, mnemonic/seed/recovery files), environment files (.env,.env.local,.env.production), SSH private keys, AWS credentials (~/.aws/credentials), git credentials (~/.git-credentials), and npm auth tokens (~/.npmrc containing authToken). All discovered secrets are exfiltrated via HTTP POST to 107[.]161[.]90[.]180:7777 as JSON.",
